    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-07T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-07T23:00:00-05:00" n="816"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0031/12–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-08T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 8, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 8—10:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1978. Oral statement issued [<hi rend="italic">handed?</hi>] December 2 [to]
                    Political Vice Foreign Minister. (ReDeptel 1522, November 23, 5 p.m.) He
                    disclaimed knowledge of statement on postwar commercial policies and said he
                    would make inquiries. On December 7 he informed us unofficially that no
                    statement had been drawn up but that proposals to do so had been made by
                    interested Chinese officials and that official response to our approach would be
                    made soon.</p>
                <p>Dr. Wu’s comments conflict with those of T. F. Tsiang who said on December 2 that
                    statement had that date been approved by Supreme National Defense Council and
                    sent to Gmo for approval. It may be that our action has caused Council to recall
                    statement for further study and possible redrafting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
